last_episode_to_air.name: The Escape
last_episode_to_air.overview: Kaz and Yeager attempt to rescue Tam from the First Order while trying to evade capture on a Star Destroyer. Meanwhile, the Colossus is in trouble and faces an impossible choice.

name: Star Wars Resistance
overview: Kazuda Xiono, a young pilot for the Resistance, is tasked with a top secret mission to investigate the First Order, a growing threat in the galaxy.

seasons.name: Specials
seasons.overview: A Series of Shorts that are related to the show

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: Season 2 takes place during the events of “The Last Jedi” leading up to “The Rise of Skywalker.” The story picks up after a harrowing escape from the First Order, as the Colossus and all its residents find themselves lost in space, pursued by Agent Tierny and Commander Pyre. Meanwhile, Tam grapples with her future and where her true allegiance lies, with her friends or the First Order.

episodes.name: The Recruit
episodes.overview: X-wing pilot Kazuda Xiono is recruited for the Resistance, but finds himself in over his head when Poe Dameron assigns him to a remote fueling station to spy on the First Order. Then, after Kaz boasts about being the best pilot around, he is forced to compete in a dangerous sky race.

guest_stars.character: First Order Comm Officer / Glem / Grevel (voice)
guest_stars.name: Dee Bradley Baker

episodes.name: The Triple Dark
episodes.overview: Kaz and BB-8 uncover information on an imminent pirate attack and must find a way to stop it.

episodes.name: Fuel for the Fire
episodes.overview: Kaz befriends a sky racer named Rucklin who pressures him to take some rare and dangerous hyperfuel hidden in Yeager’s office.

episodes.name: The High Tower
episodes.overview: The First Order arrives at the platform for mysterious reasons and Kaz and BB-8 are determined to sneak into the tower to find out what they want.

episodes.name: The Children from Tehar
episodes.overview: Kaz searches for two missing children for a sizeable reward only to discover the First Order is also hunting for them.

episodes.name: Signal from Sector Six
episodes.overview: When out on a routine training exercise, a distress signal sends Kaz and Poe to a damaged ship with strange lifeforms onboard.

episodes.name: Synara's Score
episodes.overview: On a mission to repair a vital platform defense, Kaz befriends the mysterious Synara and comes under attack by pirates.

episodes.name: The Platform Classic
episodes.overview: An upcoming race reunites Yeager with his estranged brother, Marcus, who needs to win to pay off his debt to a criminal organization.

episodes.name: Secrets and Holograms
episodes.overview: When a determined Kaz tries to discover the truth about Captain Doza, he and Torra embark on an adventure where they uncover more about the tower than either bargained for.

episodes.name: Station Theta Black
episodes.overview: When Poe and Kaz find an old First Order mining facility, BB-8 discovers the facility isn’t so abandoned.

episodes.name: Bibo
episodes.overview: Neeku adopts a strange sea creature and gets way more than he bargained for when it brings chaos to the platform.

episodes.name: Dangerous Business
episodes.overview: In exchange for parts, Kaz minds Acquisitions for Flix and Orka and comes into conflict with a shady alien customer in league with the First Order.

episodes.name: The Doza Dilemma
episodes.overview: Synara settles into life on the platform, but her pirate compatriots have other plans for her.

episodes.name: The First Order Occupation
episodes.overview: Kaz scrambles to help Synara escape the platform as the First Order sends a contingent of stormtroopers to hunt a spy.

episodes.name: The New Trooper
episodes.overview: When Kel and Eila seek out Kaz’s help after knocking out a stormtrooper, Kaz dons the trooper’s armor to protect the kids and spy on the First Order.

episodes.name: The Core Problem
episodes.overview: Poe and Kaz make an unsettling discovery and must evade the First Order when they are spotted by an enemy probe droid.

episodes.name: The Disappeared
episodes.overview: Kaz and Torra investigate the disappearance of a friend and plan to free them from the First Order.

episodes.name: Descent
episodes.overview: With secrets exposed, Yeager's crew must evade relentless troopers hunting them down and find a way to reach the Resistance.

episodes.name: No Escape (1)
episodes.overview: Kaz, Neeku, Torra devise a plan to free their friends, but it’s upended when Kaz bears witness to the full might of the First Order.

episodes.name: No Escape (2)
episodes.overview: With Neeku’s help, Kaz comes up with a risky plan to rid the Colossus of the First Order once and for all.

episodes.name: Into the Unknown
episodes.overview: After being launched into space by Kaz and crew, the Colossus encounters engineering problems, which are made worse by a mysterious stowaway.

episodes.name: A Quick Salvage Run
episodes.overview: With the Colossus in need of hyperfuel, Kaz suggests they take it from a downed First Order ship, but the salvage mission is quickly compromised when the First Order shows up.

episodes.name: Live Fire
episodes.overview: Kaz officially joins the Aces, as does Yeager -- who trains them to become better combat pilots. Tam learns what it's like to be a First Order pilot.

episodes.name: Hunt on Celsor 3
episodes.overview: The pirates volunteer to find food for the Colossus, but Kaz doesn't trust them. Kaz and Torra go on the hunt, but run into big problems.

episodes.name: The Engineer
episodes.overview: Kaz and Neeku discover Nena, a Nikto engineer in need of assistance who barely escaped a First Order attack.

episodes.name: From Beneath
episodes.overview: Flix takes Kaz and crew to his home world to acquire fuel from his family's refinery, only to discover the family's drilling has awoken something monstrous.

episodes.name: The Relic Raiders
episodes.overview: When Kaz and team arrives on a mysterious planet to buy supplies, they find the outpost has been abandoned and a secret Sith Temple has been raised.

episodes.name: Rendezvous Point
episodes.overview: Doza attempts to meet a Resistance pilot from his past, but the pilot has been captured by the First Order.

episodes.name: The Voxx Vortex 5000
episodes.overview: With the Colossus running out of money, Hype risks everything by taking the Aces to race at Vranki's Casino, run by Vranki the Hutt.

episodes.name: Kaz's Curse
episodes.overview: A pirate curses Kaz, causing him danger at every turn. Kaz is soon forced to seek Mika Grey for help, but Kaz's curse gets worse when the Guavian Death Gang appears.

episodes.name: Station to Station
episodes.overview: Kaz and Neeku sneak onto a First Order refueling station in order to take an important piece of tech. Plans go awry when they run into Tam and General Hux.

episodes.name: The Missing Agent
episodes.overview: Kaz, Yeager and Synara trace a distress call to a planet where a Resistance agent has gone missing. Things only get worse as a mysterious bounty hunter starts hunting them.

episodes.name: Breakout
episodes.overview: Kaz and Norath try to help their friends while being pursued by a deadly bounty hunter.

episodes.name: The Mutiny
episodes.overview: Kragan buys a secret weapon to capture the Colossus and take over. When Synara discovers this plan, she tries to warn Kaz and crew, but it may be too late.

episodes.name: The New World
episodes.overview: Doza takes the Colossus to a hidden world on the outer rim, only to find it’s inhabited by beings who don’t like them.

episodes.name: No Place Safe
episodes.overview: Kaz decides to join up with Poe and the Resistance, but things go awry when he discovers the First Order has located the Colossus.

episodes.name: Rebuilding the Resistance
episodes.overview: Resistance recruits need an escort getting off of Dantooine, but, unfortunately, Tam is assigned to destroy the recruits.

episodes.name: The Escape
episodes.overview: Kaz and Yeager attempt to rescue Tam from the First Order while trying to evade capture on a Star Destroyer. Meanwhile, the Colossus is in trouble and faces an impossible choice.
